This README file contains information on the contents of the
openuxas layer.

Please see the corresponding sections below for details.


Dependencies
============

This layer depends on:

  URI: git://git.openembedded.org/bitbake
  branch: pyro

  URI: git://git.openembedded.org/openembedded-core
  layers: meta
  branch: pyro

  URI: https://github.com/acfoltzer/meta-openembedded.git
  layers: meta-oe meta-python
  branch: meson-updates


Patches
=======

Please submit any patches against the openuxas layer to GitHub


Table of Contents
=================

  I. Adding the openuxas layer to your build
 II. Misc


I. Adding the openuxas layer to your build
=================================================

In order to use this layer, you need to make the build system aware of
it.

Assuming the openuxas layer exists at the top-level of your
yocto build tree, you can add it to the build system by adding the
location of the openuxas layer to bblayers.conf, along with any
other layers needed. e.g.:

  BBLAYERS ?= " \
    /path/to/yocto/meta \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-poky \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-yocto-bsp \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-openuxas \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-openembedded/meta-oe \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-openembedded/meta-python \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-openuxas \
    "
